The article is a press gaggle by a senior administration official discussing the President's meetings with Prime Minister Manning of Trinidad and Tobago and the CARICOM (Caribbean Community). The discussions focused on topics such as the economic financial crisis, trade relations, energy, security issues, and drug trafficking. The President expressed a desire to strengthen energy and security ties with Trinidad and Tobago and develop partnerships with Latin America and the Caribbean to address common challenges. The CARICOM meeting covered issues relating to the global financial crisis, bottom-up economic growth, security partnerships, climate change, Cuba, and Haiti. The President emphasized his interest in a new relationship with Cuba and the need for change from the Cuban side. There was also a discussion on helping Haiti develop self-sustained economic growth.